\subsection{\href{https://beta.lmfdb.org/knowledge/show/intro.direct_sql}{Direct SQL connection}}
\begin{definition}\label{intro.direct_sql}
\uses{}
You can open a direct connection to a read-only copy of the LMFDB's PostgreSQL database, using the SQL Mirror access information below.  There are three ways to do this:

\begin{itemize}
\item  You can exploit standard \href{https://wiki.postgresql.org/wiki/PostgreSQL_Clients}{third-party tools} or \href{https://wiki.postgresql.org/wiki/List_of_drivers}{programming language drivers} for working with \href{https://www.postgresql.org/}{PostgreSQL} databases; these require knowledge of SQL.
\item  You can use the \href{https://github.com/roed314/lmfdb-lite}{lmfdb-lite} library, which provides a pure Python interface to the SQL mirror using dictionaries, equivalent to that used in the LMFDB source code.
\item  You can \href{https://github.com/LMFDB/lmfdb/blob/main/GettingStarted.md}{install the LMFDB web front-end locally}.  This provides a \href{https://www.sagemath.org/}{SageMath} interface to the LMFDB via the mirror similar to lmfdb-lite and provides access to the entire LMFDB code base, which includes methods that can be used to create python objects corresponding to mathematical objects stored in the LMFDB.
\end{itemize}
\end{definition}


